by: dragon-ai-agent\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:7770028\nname: obsolete glycoprotein cargo receptor activity\nnamespace: molecular_function\ndef: \"OBSOLETE. Binding specifically to a glycoprotein (cargo) to deliver it to a transport vesicle. Glycoprotein cargo receptors span membranes, binding simultaneously to cargo molecules and coat adaptors, to efficiently recruit the cargo molecules to nascent vesicles.\" [PMID:41203586]\ncomment: The reason for obsoletion is that this term was added in error. Most vesicle cargo are glycoproteins, so classifying cargo receptors by glycoprotein substrate introduces an additional, unhelpful axis of classification. Cargo receptor activities should instead be organized by transport domain (i.e., the vesicles they connect cargo to), with substrates captured via has_input.\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31948\" xsd:anyURI\nis_obsolete: true\nreplaced_by: GO:0038024\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:7770029\nname: phosphatidylserine receptor activity\nnamespace: molecular_function\ndef: \"Combining with phosphatidylserine and transmitting the signal from one side of the membrane to the other to initiate a change in cell activity.\" [PMID:17960135, PMID:18082433]\nis_a: GO:0004888 ! transmembrane signaling receptor activity\nrelationship: has_part GO:0001786 ! phosphatidylserine binding\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31055\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: dragon-ai-agent\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:7770030\nname: rod photoreceptor phosphodiesterase 6 complex\nnamespace: cellular_component\ndef: \"A heterotetrameric cGMP phosphodiesterase complex found in the disc membranes of rod photoreceptor outer segments. It consists of two catalytic subunits, PDE6A and PDE6B, and two inhibitory gamma-subunits, PDE6G. In response to activation by transducin, the complex hydrolyzes cyclic GMP, thereby mediating the light-induced closure of cGMP-gated ion channels during rod phototransduction.\" [PMID:38159849]\nsynonym: \"rod PDE6 complex\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"rod photoreceptor PDE6 complex\" EXACT []\nis_a: GO:0032991 ! protein-containing complex\nrelationship: part_of GO:0120202 ! rod photoreceptor disc membrane\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31081\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: dragon-ai-agent\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:7770031\nname: sodium ion sequestering activity\nnamespace: molecular_function\ndef: \"Binding to a sodium ion to prevent it from interacting with other partners or to inhibit its localization to the area of the cell or complex where it is active.\" [PMID:25689889]\nintersection_of: GO:0140313 ! molecular sequestering activity\nintersection_of: has_part GO:0031402 ! sodium ion binding\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31137\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: dragon-ai-agent\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:7770032\nname: obsolete tyramine transport\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"OBSOLETE. The directed movement of tyramine into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore. Tyramine is a monoamine neurotransmitter occurring predominantly in invertebrates.\" [PMID:15849736, PMID:32305263, PMID:9870940]\ncomment: The reason for obsoletion is that this is an unnecessary grouping term and annotations should be made to more mechanism/location specific terms.\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31143\" xsd:anyURI\nis_obsolete: true\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:7770033\nname: octopamine transport\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"The directed movement of octopamine into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore. Octopamine is a monoamine neurotransmitter occurring predominantly in invertebrates.\" [PMID:15849736, PMID:32305263, PMID:9870940]\nintersection_of: GO:0006810 ! transport\nintersection_of: